{"key":"post-11264529","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11264529</id>\n<content>If the light heats up the terrarium that much, you're probably using an incandescent light bulb, which is almost as bad as no light at all.&amp;nbsp; Use fluorescent.&amp;nbsp; That's probably also why your humidity is low.&amp;nbsp; For a given amount of moisture in the air, a 20F temperature rise will cut the relative humidity in half.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Air exchange is the number one pinning trigger, so you need more holes or to fan more.&amp;nbsp; Get rid of any heating pads etc.&amp;nbsp; If you're growing in your house, they're not necessary, and actually counterproductive.&amp;nbsp; It's the reason you have condensation, even though your humidity is too low.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11266004</next>\n<prev>11264525</prev>\n<first>11264412</first>\n<last>11266888</last>\n<when>1255792246</when>\n<utime>10/17/09 06:10 PM</utime>\n</post>"}